Use SERVICE_PROTOCOL variable in the devstack plugin

Vitrage service be deployed with TLS in Devstack, so we need to honor
SERVICE_PROTOCOL variable to set correct value for VITRAGE_SERVICE_PROTOCOL

commit_message:
Fix listing SOFT_DELETED servers by vm_state.

Currently, query SOFT_DELETED instances by 'vm_state' does not work,
because in nova.api.openstack.compute.servers.ServersController._get_servers,
nova does not verify 'vm_state' the same way as verifying 'status'.

So in this fix patch, we extend vm_states to statuses, and verify the two
query params together.

Change-Id: I255323b41ef232f38384f268ca5ce6da497b9eb1
Related-Bug: #1789455
Closes-Bug: #1857447
Signed-off-by: Fan Zhang <zh.f@outlook.com>

commit_message:
Drop unused remnants of the hosts-config bits

Hosts entries are used to be configured via tripleo_ansible's
tripleo_hosts_entries.

Ifd4bc4ce5618587c341ecbf37f82777ae6fc2f4a removed the use
of WRITE_HOSTS, which currently makes hosts-config.yaml "headless" and
taking no real data for the hosts-config.sh template that generates
outputs for OS::TripleO::Hosts::SoftwareConfig.

Also I606e0f27f9f9ae9d85bc0fc653f8985eb734d004 removed the use of
HOST_ENTRY, which makes the hosts-config.sh taking an empty value for
it.

Probably that all makes it safe now to remove any use of
hosts-config.sh and hosts-config.yaml and corresponding
OS::TripleO::Hosts::SoftwareConfig completely.

Change-Id: Id04767ae0c32caf62271cf564608350974fefd1b
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Use lists for storing host entries in Heat

This simplifies all the split/join transformations and improves the
memory footprint to a reduced list of unique entries for
HostsEntryValue (originally required for storing the ultimate data for
hosts entries in a form of a quite long single-line string value).

That improves the hosts entries processing for large scale deployments
and removes possible limitations to the sizes of strings.

Closes-bug: #1869375
Change-Id: I5ac498621e9e3c49def565744a7b521cb2cc5c25
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

subject: Do not throw KeyError if port_security is not set
revisions:
[{'created': '2020-04-01 00:47:35.000000000', 'message': "Do not throw KeyError if port_security is not set

When port_security is turned on in an existing deployment, there will be
no DB entry for the existing ports. If a sync is run then, it throw a
KeyError.

Treat port_security as False if row isn't found.

Change-Id: Ic1edc8eb89fb1efe877769cd9c46ca39f70caabe
"}]
commit_message:
Do not throw KeyError if port_security is not set

When port_security is turned on in an existing deployment, there will be
no DB entry for the existing ports. If a sync is run then, it throw a
KeyError.

Treat port_security as False if row isn't found.

Change-Id: Ic1edc8eb89fb1efe877769cd9c46ca39f70caabe

revisions:
[{'created': '2020-02-25 10:37:04.000000000', 'message': 'Implements attribute filters list API

For certain resources,like VNF Packages,representations can become
quite big.In these cases, it is desired to reduce the amount of data
exchanged over the interface and processed by the API consumer.

An attribute selector i.e filter, allows the API consumer to choose
which attributes it wants to be contained in the response. Only
attributes that are not required to be present, i.e. those with
a lower bound of zero on their cardinality (e.g. 0..1, 0..N)
and that are not conditionally mandatory, are allowed to be omitted
as part of the selection process.

This patch implements attribute filtering for the GET method for
VNF packages.

The get method supports the following parameters.
*filter: Filter criterion built with attributes of VNF Package and
REST operators
*all_fields: Return all fields
*fields=<list> : Return fields specified in the <list>
*exclude_fields=<list>: Return fields not specified in the <list>
*exclude_default parameters: Return all fields except default fields
*exclude_default and fields=<list>: Return all fields except default
fields and fields in the <list>
*When no parameter is specified it is treated as exclude_default.

For pagination the get method supports the following parameters
*nextpage_opaque_marker: Specifies the current page. Default is 0
*per_page: Specifies the number of VNF Packages in one page.
Default is 1000
Pagination supported is forward. i.e. the rel is set to 'next' and
finally to 'last'.
Pagination is implemented according to RFC 5988 Page 6.
The attributes used for filtering of VNF Packages are shown below
in the form of <field>:<parent model>:

    'id':'VnfPackage',
    'onboardingState':'VnfPackage',
    'operationalState':'VnfPackage',
    'usageState':'VnfPackage',
    'checksum/algorithm' : 'VnfPackage',
    'checksum/hash' : 'VnfPackage',
    'softwareImages/id': 'VnfSoftwareImage'
    'softwareImages/imagePath':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/diskFormat':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/userMetadata':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/id':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/size':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/name':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/checksum/hash':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/checksum/algorithm':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/minDisk':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/version':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/provider':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/minRAM' :'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'softwareImages/containerFormat':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'vnfProvider':'VnfPackageVnfd',
    'vnfProductName' :'VnfPackageVnfd',
    'vnfdId':'VnfPackageVnfd',
    'vnfSoftwareVersion':'VnfPackageVnfd',
    'vnfdVersion':'VnfPackageVnfd',
    'userDefinedData':'VnfPackageUserData'

The operators used for filtering are:

	eq,neq,in,nin,gt,gte,it,lte,cont,ncont

Multiple filtering attributes are connected using |(OR) or ;(AND)

Sample url using attribute filtering

curl -g -G -i -X  GET http://10.0.2.15:9890/vnfpkgm/v1/vnf_packages
--data-urlencode 'filter=(eq,onboardingState,'onboarded_1')|
(eq,softwareImages/checksum/algorithm,'sha-256')|
(eq,vnfProvider,'NTT_NS_lab')'
--data-urlencode 'nextpage_opaque_marker=1'
--data-urlencode 'per_page=1' -H? "User-Agent: python-tackerclient"
-H "Accept: application/json" -H "X-Auth-Token:xxxx"

Change-Id: I637fb4ec28264f70b0f3344120ebca1c85aff61f
Depends-On: If65e7aff4a90e2c8ebd46cc43a21b2860a35b909

WIP Implements attribute filters list API

For certain resources,like VNF Packages,representations can become
quite big.In these cases, it is desired to reduce the amount of data
exchanged over the interface and processed by the API consumer.

An attribute selector i.e filter, allows the API consumer to choose

*exclude_default parameters: Return all fields except default fields
*exclude_default and fields=<list>: Return all fields except default
fields and fields in the <list>
*When no parameter is specified it is treated as exclude_default.

For pagination the get method supports the following parameters
*nextpage_opaque_marker: Specifies the current page. Default is 0
*per_page: Specifies the number of VNF Packages in one page.
Default is 1000
Pagination supported is forward. i.e. the rel is set to 'next' and
finally to 'last'.
Pagination is implemented according to RFC 5988 Page 6.

    'softwareImages/containerFormat':'VnfSoftwareImage',
    'vnfProvider':'VnfPackageVnfd',

commit_message:
Add test coverage of existing hypervisors policies

Current tests do not have good test coverage of existing policies.
Either tests for policies do not exist or if they exist then they
do not cover the actual negative and positive testing.

For Example, if any policy with default rule as admin only then
test should verify:
- policy check pass with context having admin or server owner
- policy check fail with context having non-admin and not server owner

As discussed in policy-defaults-refresh, to change the policies
with new default roles and scope_type, we need to have the enough
testing coverage of existing policy behavior.

When we will add the scope_type in policies or new default roles,
then these test coverage will be extended to adopt the new changes
and also make sure we do not break the existing behavior.

This commit covers the testing coverage of existing hypervisors policies.

Partial implement blueprint policy-defaults-refresh

Change-Id: Ieb5e27ccec000f6d6bb598aa00a4a17e0f334aad

commit_message:
Set tox_constraints_file for npm jobs and integration tests

npm jobs and integration tests always try to use the constraints
from releases.openstack.org and do not pick up the change in the gate
even when Depends-On is specified.

For npm jobs, https://review.opendev.org/#/c/709414/ allows us to pass
tox_constraints_file when creating the envvar of the constraints file.
This commit consumes it.

Change-Id: I396073182ff1e63df12ebb79c3ddd646277ddadf
(cherry picked from commit 7f26bfcbb1f88f81c022940a4068321b1cda1c3c)

commit_message:
Ensure consistency with hostname comparison

It might happen an operator wants to get «camelcased» hostname.

Since the RFC[1] states "no distinction is made between upper and lower
case", we have to ensure string comparisons made in ansible are all
lowered.

[1] https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc952

Closes-Bug: #1869360
Change-Id: I988a8ce958f9fb21115aacde526c2dc89a3c8d66
(cherry picked from commit e236ff0cf97d370dcad74467caa2d88d133dc6c1)

commit_message:
Add always tags for hieradata render in external upgrade.

When executing the external-upgrade command, if some of the
external_upgrade_tasks make use of the all_nodes vars (*_short_node_names
for example) then the command fails as these variables weren't
rendered. This only happens when we run the external-upgrade command
passing --tags, as the facts tags are being skipped.

This patch adds the always tags into those tasks which miss it for
external_upgrade_steps_playbook.yaml.

Change-Id: I0913df554b75d25215d5ae6547b939ad0356df3c
(cherry picked from commit e8a2dcbb8659c764ec6f68fb2a73fc7bbb575756)

revisions:
[{'created': '2020-03-17 11:41:43.000000000', 'message': 'HA: minor update of arbitrary container image name

HA services get their container image name from a pacemaker
resource configuration. This image name is shared between
all cluster nodes.

To achieve image update without service disruption, a pacemaker
resource is configured to use an intermediate image name
"<registry>/<namespace>/<servicename>:pcmklatest" pointing to
the real image name configured in Heat. This tag can then be
updated independently on every node during the minor update.

In order to support the same rolling update when the <namespace>
changes in the container image, we need a similar floating
approach for the prefix part of the container image.

Introduce a new Heat parameter ClusterCommonTag that, when enabled,
sets the intermediate image name to
"cluster-common-tag/<servicename>:pcmklatest". By default, this
parameter is disabled and the original naming scheme is conserved.

Note: by introducing this new naming scheme, we stop seeing a
meaningful image name prefix when doing a "pcs status", but since
we already can't tell what image ID the :pcmklatest tag points to,
we don't lose much information really.

commit_message:
HA: minor update of arbitrary container image name

HA services get their container image name from a pacemaker
resource configuration. This image name is shared between
all cluster nodes.

To achieve image update without service disruption, a pacemaker
resource is configured to use an intermediate image name
"<registry>/<namespace>/<servicename>:pcmklatest" pointing to
the real image name configured in Heat. This tag can then be
updated independently on every node during the minor update.

In order to support the same rolling update when the <namespace>
changes in the container image, we need a similar floating
approach for the prefix part of the container image.

Introduce a new Heat parameter ClusterCommonTag that, when enabled,
sets the intermediate image name to
"cluster-common-tag/<servicename>:pcmklatest". By default, this
parameter is disabled and the original naming scheme is conserved.

Note: by introducing this new naming scheme, we stop seeing a
meaningful image name prefix when doing a "pcs status", but since
we already can't tell what image ID the :pcmklatest tag points to,
we don't lose much information really.

Related-Bug: #1854730

Change-Id: Id369154d147cd5cf0a6f997bf806084fc7580e01
(cherry picked from commit 2487becc6a6d263e55c9a642d51994a72c1cb9aa)

commit_message:
Prevent duplicated hosts in overcloudrc no_proxy

When an operator run `source overcloudrc` then `source stackrc`,
ENV['no_proxy'] keep having overcloud information because stackrc
doesn't include no_proxy line.
If they run deploym commands like overcloud deploy with that situation,
the command is executed with ENV['no_proxy'] including overcloud hosts.
This generates overcloudrc with duplicated host in no_proxy line,
because no_proxy in overcloudrc is generated by joining ENV['no_proxy']
and rquired overcloud hosts.

This patch makes sure that duplicated hosts are removed before they get
dumped into no_proxy parameter.

Change-Id: I3c5ba5f02e18f68f27580499729712d1652a86ba

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary references to optional cinder templates

Cinder has many templates for its various backend drivers, and they
all default to OS::Heat::None in the resource registry. There's no
need to mention them in most env files, and removing the references
reduces maintenance work when cinder's list of backend templates
changes (which it tends to do).

Change-Id: I794c7d9bd024fd12289571f2bfde16230f8fc32c

the default ENTRYPOINT of the docker image.

commit_message:
Cleanup Python 2.7 support

OpenStack is dropping the py2.7 support in ussuri cycle.

Make a few cleanups:
- Remove python 2.7 stanza from setup.py
- Add python-requires to setup.cfg so that pypi and pip know
  about support Python version
- Remove ancient sections from setup.cfg
- Remove version_info setting from conf.py, openstackdocstheme does this
  automatically nowadays.

Change-Id: I5b9c159752c932f874015f20822862c70562c2bd

commit_message:
Match hostname when doing node delete

``overcloud node delete`` at present matches the provided nova
instance ids with existing severs to build the heat blacklist.
This patch would allow users to also use hostnames when deleting
nodes. This will work with deployed servers and scale_playbook.yaml
that matches host pattern.

Partial-Bug: #1869089
Change-Id: I3066689facc169125ade29156190cb98910f32b8

commit_message:
Bump compute rpcapi version and reduce Cyborg calls.

The _get_bound_arq_resources() in the compute manager [1] calls Cyborg
up to 3 times: once to get the accelerator request (ARQ) UUIDs for the
instance, and then once or twice to get all ARQs with completed bindings.

The first call can be eliminated by passing the ARQs from the conductor
to the compute manager as an additional parameter in
build_and_run_instance(). This requires a bump in compute rpcapi version.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/631244/54/nova/compute/manager.py@2652

Blueprint: nova-cyborg-interaction

Change-Id: I26395d57bd4ba55276b7514baa808f9888639e11

commit_message:
Add new default roles in os-agents policies

This adds new defaults roles in os-agents API policies. This policy
is default to system admin role. Policy rules are made more granular
to adopt the new defaults.

Partial implement blueprint policy-defaults-refresh

Change-Id: I9b094ecd3c5ff4f56ecfafb72c2a660b4146035f

commit_message:
Fail NetworkConfig task on timeout

Running os-net-config as async, with failed_when as false
results in undefined variable error if async task times out.
Instead of ignoring failure of task, check for the
presense of results of the command execution 'rc', if it
is not defined, then rest of the tasks are not useful.
Closes-Bug: #1862627

Change-Id: Ibbcde856ac69bf73a47086d95a52c3b1a0d10911

commit_message:
Add support for list data type

In ETSI tosca definition, node type “tosca.nodes.nfv.VNF” has
property “vnfm_info” that is defined as of type list.

Definition given in etsi_nfv_sol001_vnfd_types.yaml:
tosca.nodes.nfv.VNF:
    properties:
      vnfm_info:
        type: list
        required: true

Example:
tosca.nodes.nfv.VNF:
    properties:
      vnfm_info: [vnfm1, vnfm2]

Added translation support for list data type.

Change-Id: I02a4ba46da588ef7c1ac36a15d7cd537187e3ecc

commit_message:
Update compute instance-usage and agents tests to adopt new policies

Nova is moving to new policy defaults in ussuri[1] where
few polciies are made more granular to adopt the new defaults.

With granularity in few policies make change in policy name so
we have update the patrole tests to start checking against the
new policy names from ussuri onwards.

This commit updates the os-instance-usage-audit-log and os-agents tests
to move to new policies from ussuri onwards.

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/nova-specs/specs/ussuri/approved/policy-defaults-refresh.html

Change-Id: I9eb2964c0ffb7022d52fc94c97bbd25c76b6d6d8

commit_message:
Neutron ML2/OVN: Add support to enable IGMP Snooping

Right now, there's no way to drive the IGMP Snooping knob in
Neutron from THT. This patch is adding a new parameter that
defaults to False for ML2/OVN deployments.

Change-Id: I835f8faf51dc47b300d5ebdc4e821f8c40daf065
Closes-Bug: #1868569
Signed-off-by: Daniel Alvarez <dalvarez@redhat.com>
(cherry picked from commit d5be566b3db3b288534e6cb5f3290416e2731784)

commit_message:
config-download timeout should KILL the process.

The timeout command defaults to using TERM which does
not always ensure that it will end soon enough. The
ansible-playbook command should end as soon as possible.

Change-Id: I0f97772434040f04f9495239b9a432c1ac062555
Closes-Bug: #1867968
Signed-off-by: Luke Short <ekultails@gmail.com>
(cherry picked from commit 7be36f305107c0bfb4e403f5df4226635e34dffa)
(cherry picked from commit 9faf10dd844b13d002b0d16413935fceae46ed4e)

commit_message:
Remove kwargs validation for identity project updates

Keystone supports setting custom properties when updating projects [1].  This
change removes the check in openstacksdk cloud that prevents users from
passing in custom kwargs when calling update_project.

[1] https://opendev.org/openstack/keystone/src/branch/master/keystone/resource/schema.py#L76

Change-Id: I8b193d10b599c484447a7f5e0e0377276c6139d8
Story: 2007469
Task: 39157

commit_message:
[Mariadb] Initialize variable

There are scenarios where the wsrep_rec_pos variable is being returned
without it being first initialized when the .communicate() method
returns a blank. This patchset sets up a default initialization, so
the readiness check does not error out with an exception.

Change-Id: Ifea922f446bf3cbc9220f39a41dffc2763e6a5f3
Signed-off-by: Tin Lam <tin@irrational.io>

revisions:
[{'created': '2020-03-31 15:33:38.000000000', 'message': 'Create a new parameter for the HAProxy external network

In the standalone config, there is no external network defined.
This leaves the hieradata cloud_name_external undefined, resulting in
an error when we are using the haproxy-public-tls-certmonger template
to create new public certs through haproxy.

Using the PublicNetwork allows us to get the right network for haproxy
in all cases to specify the network and fqdn to use for public certmonger
certificates.

Co-Authored-By: Grzegorz Grasza <xek@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I8778402bbb7a670c4aa95671c6017dff356238d4
(cherry picked from commit e5f51815c5a8f9698092aee49b966018faa5b414)
'}]
commit_message:
Create a new parameter for the HAProxy external network

In the standalone config, there is no external network defined.
This leaves the hieradata cloud_name_external undefined, resulting in
an error when we are using the haproxy-public-tls-certmonger template
to create new public certs through haproxy.

Using the PublicNetwork allows us to get the right network for haproxy
in all cases to specify the network and fqdn to use for public certmonger
certificates.

Co-Authored-By: Grzegorz Grasza <xek@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I8778402bbb7a670c4aa95671c6017dff356238d4
(cherry picked from commit e5f51815c5a8f9698092aee49b966018faa5b414)

We do not have much active contributors in patrole now and waiting

commit_message:
Changing the review policy to approve with single +2

We do not have much active contributors in patrole now and waiting
for second +2 is time taking and end up not merging the patches.

let's change the patch merge policy to require only single +2.

Once we have enough contributors then we can change it back to two +2.

Change-Id: I60d5e4ac559511d59088f1a9f06ca2022eabd609

commit_message:
Normalize the 'undercloud-passwords.conf' return data

This change normalizes our client return formation by ensuring we're always
using the configured output path as defined within our constants.

Closes-Bug: #1868619

Change-Id: Ied051214c4d3f2a695d58a6cde6180f040ca02d4
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kecarter@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Switch scenario001-multinode-containers to LVM-based bluestore

scenario001-multinode was still using a loopback device directly
which is no longer supported as per the move to ceph-volume which
was documented in RH BZ 1666822. scenario00{1,4}-standalone were
updated to deal with this by passing precreated lvm_volumes to
CephAnsibleDisksConfig but scenario001-multinode was not. This
change brings it back up to date for deploying bluestore with
ceph-volume.

Change-Id: I1f0420b8d48d9a2e8327c78daf48449537e3b842

commit_message:
Allow override of mysql/galera open files limit

This commit removes the hard coded value of open-file-limit (16384)
and allows operators to override it via:

tripleo::profile::pacemaker::database::mysql::open_files_limit
tripleo::profile::pacemaker::database::mysql_bundle::open_files_limit

Change-Id: I4927eb65a2dc1b5a86fc2141c7b2713f36ad49de
Resolves: rhbz#1812969

commit_message:
Replace deprecated gnocchi::storage::coordination_url

The gnocchi::storage::corrdination_url parameter was deprecated to be
replaced by the gnocchi::coordination_url parameter.
This patch make puppet-tripleo to use the new parameter instead of the
deprecated one.

Depends-on: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/713448/
Change-Id: I2bbe95375c465aea8d2fe91b31897541ed998ae7

commit_message:
baremetal provision expose concurrency and timeout

These arguments are available in the workflow but are not exposed as
arguments. This change fixes that, allowing users to tune for their
environment.

The new ansible version of this command already has these arguments
(next change in this series)

commit_message:
Revert "Stop using swift temp url for config transport"

This switch seems to be creating issues with upgrades, where a number of
software deployments are deleted concurrently while updating the config
transport for the server. Switching the config transport does not work
with convergence heat and should be fixed in heat. We can revert this
now, as we still use swift for other stuff in the undercloud. Can be
changed once the issue is fixed in heat.

It also reverts the following dependant commit.

Revert "Cleanup SoftwareConfigTransport"

This reverts commit (1821c01846a20da331959ff49fe8536f1e1bf86a and
3ea9dd4040686b7c2ec82f7e7e467e0b3c3bd2a7)

Closes-Bug: #1869335
Change-Id: I835c8be3eecce91f8a370d036bf1085bc445e01d
(cherry picked from commit 6ff119ddacdeb55d1637ad8c6557225732c31d22)

commit_message:
Only run horizon check for horizon changes

This change sets the files attribute for the zuul job that runs
the horizon check to only run that check when a file change is made
under the horizon chart directory.

commit_message:
Consistent timestamp format for all datasources

All timestamps in Vitrage should be of the same format:
'%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ'

This is needed so webhooks will know what format to expect.

Story: 1776181
Task: 22405


Change-Id: I9849ce0850de46f928a7c01009c7738976aa3478
(cherry picked from commit 75fb4d12133f4f7d304ded5612bbf96bb9438d2e)

commit_message:
Follow up for I4660043fcccec6721e197c4d77390744e356c59e

This patch addresses nits from
I4660043fcccec6721e197c4d77390744e356c59e.

It also changes ctrlplane_address to ctlplane_address to bring it
inline with the exsting ctlplane_ssh_* options. It is NOT POLITE to do
so, but in practice, nothig is actually using the new ctrlplane
option in the wild yet, so it should be safe.

Change-Id: I9e06917a3ca6476fe4204f31e4121590140e90c9

Update hacking for Python3

The repo is Python 3 now, so update hacking to version 3.0 which
supports Python 3.

Fix problems found.

Update local hacking checks for new flake8.

Remove hacking and friends from lower-constraints, it's not needed
there for co-installing.

Change-Id: I3d250ba82cc14f163f4295381b9b9c232486ac9f

commit_message:
Importing keyrings from files rather than from mons

This change permits users to specify a directory where the keyrings are
located.
It is useful when openstack-ansible have no ssh access to the ceph
cluster.

Change-Id: I6693a7f9d0bc7fe1e20eee53a96de8df8985e148
(cherry picked from commit db3e9536d403727a964c5cc404e62cff37845c84)

commit_message:
Fix pyScss version in lower-constraints.txt

Horizon requires  pyScss>=1.3.7 [1] but lower-constraints.txt
in sahara-dashboard uses pyScss 1.3.4 which can cause the
failure in future. So this patch update pyScss version in
lower-constraints.txt to sync the change.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/715241/

Change-Id: Ia2415a21f643648ebd02644224ec44dcc773713a

commit_message:
Update compute os-agents tests to adopt new policies

Nova is moving to new policy defaults in ussuri[1] where
few polciies are made more granular to adopt the new defaults.

With granularity in few policies make change in policy name so
we have update the patrole tests to start checking against the
new policy names from ussuri onwards.

This commit updates the os-agents tests to move to new policies
from ussuri onwards.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/701648/

[1] https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/nova-specs/specs/ussuri/approved/policy-defaults-refresh.html

Change-Id: I845e35fcb8c310ec0859ed2a696bcda5e36bbe03

[{'created': '2020-03-25 17:43:32.000000000', 'message': 'Filter subnet by segment ID only if exists

In "_query_filter_by_fixed_ips_segment", the subnet query should be
filtered by segment ID only if exists.

The "segment_id" field (from the "subnet" DB register) is a string.
As reported in the related bug, PostgreSQL does not accept to compare
this field with a boolean value ("false"). This patch avoids the
previous situation where the DB WHERE statement was trying to compare
a string and a boolean:

  operator does not exist: character varying = boolean
  LINE 5: WHERE anon_1.subnets_segment_id = false
  No operator matches the given name and argument type(s). You might \
    need to add explicit type casts.

Change-Id: I1ff29eb45c6663885c2b8a126a3669e75b920c98
Closes-Bug: #1869034

commit_message:
Filter subnet by segment ID or None

In "_query_filter_by_fixed_ips_segment", the subnet query should be
filtered by segment ID if exists, or None otherwise.

The "segment_id" field (from the "subnet" DB register) is a string.
As reported in the related bug, PostgreSQL does not accept to compare
this field with a boolean value ("false"). This patch avoids the
previous situation where the DB WHERE statement was trying to compare
a string and a boolean:

  operator does not exist: character varying = boolean
  LINE 5: WHERE anon_1.subnets_segment_id = false
  No operator matches the given name and argument type(s). You might \
    need to add explicit type casts.

Change-Id: I1ff29eb45c6663885c2b8a126a3669e75b920c98
Closes-Bug: #1869034

commit_message:
PowerMax Driver - Legacy volume not found

The equals check is too stringent for legacy pre Pike volumes
after an upgrade.  Pre PIke is SMI-S, Pike and later is REST
and identifier name is persisted differently.

Change-Id: I963ad219c2e3b1c9c5edaa8f7e0d3dea911ecd8e
Closes-Bug: #1867163
(cherry picked from commit 4296ea130e1055d608b11b44cbff21358804ae7d)

commit_message:
Add new default roles in os-ips policies

This adds new defaults roles in os-ips API policies.
This policy is default to PROJECT_MEMBER_OR_SYSTEM_ADMIN role.

Policy rules are made more granular to adopt the new defaults.

Also add tests to simulates the future where we drop the deprecation
fall back in the policy by overriding the rules with a version where
there are no deprecated rule options. Operators can do the same by
adding overrides in their policy files that match the default but
stop the rule deprecation fallback from happening.

Partial implement blueprint policy-defaults-refresh

Change-Id: If6badcfa40c56ad39f3dd8c18c8a76a364b0152a

[Community goal] Update contributor documentation

As the Ussuri goal we have an OpenStack project wide contributing
documentation template [1]. Nova has its own contributor documentation
so this patch adds the new contributing.rst according to the global
template and links the sections in it to the existing Nova contributor
documentation.

Also the top level CONTRIBUTING.rst template has been changed in the
cookiecutter repo[2]. So this patch updates the CONTRIBUTING.rst according
to the new template.

[1] https://opendev.org/openstack/cookiecutter/src/branch/master/%7b%7bcookiecutter.repo_name%7d%7d/doc/source/contributor/contributing.rst
[2] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/696001

Task: #38541

commit_message:
mech_driver.OVNMechanismDriver "_ovn_client" is a read-only property

mech_driver.OVNMechanismDriver "_ovn_client" is not a class member but
a read-only property and can't be assigned.

Change-Id: I6fdd9d929e75a6092e0a874b8ffcf283c64b076a
Closes-Bug: #1869342

commit_message:
Introduce scope_types in os-ips

oslo.policy introduced the scope_type feature which can
control the access level at system-level and project-level.
 - https://docs.openstack.org/oslo.policy/latest/user/usage.html#setting-scope
 - http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/keystone-specs/specs/keystone/queens/system-scope.html

Appropriate scope_type for nova case:
- https://specs.openstack.org/openstack/nova-specs/specs/ussuri/approved/policy-defaults-refresh.html#scope

This commit introduce scope_type for os-ips API policies
as 'system' and 'project'.

Partial implement blueprint policy-defaults-refresh

Change-Id: I153be2126a07add7544412e8dcd2753bdd180293

[{'created': '2020-03-27 16:40:50.000000000', 'message': 'Add test coverage of existing ips policies

Current tests do not have good test coverage of existing policies.
Either tests for policies do not exist or if they exist then they
do not cover the actual negative and positive testing.

For Example, if any policy with default rule as admin only then
test should verify:
- policy check pass with context having admin or server owner
- policy check fail with context having non-admin and not server owner

As discussed in policy-defaults-refresh, to change the policies
with new default roles and scope_type, we need to have the enough
testing coverage of existing policy behavior.

When we will add the scope_type in policies or new default roles,
then these test coverage will be extended to adopt the new changes
and also make sure we do not break the existing behavior.

This commit covers the testing coverage of existing ips policies.

Partial implement blueprint policy-defaults-refresh

commit_message:
Add test coverage of existing ips policies

Current tests do not have good test coverage of existing policies.
Either tests for policies do not exist or if they exist then they
do not cover the actual negative and positive testing.

For Example, if any policy with default rule as admin only then
test should verify:
- policy check pass with context having admin or server owner
- policy check fail with context having non-admin and not server owner

As discussed in policy-defaults-refresh, to change the policies
with new default roles and scope_type, we need to have the enough
testing coverage of existing policy behavior.

When we will add the scope_type in policies or new default roles,
then these test coverage will be extended to adopt the new changes
and also make sure we do not break the existing behavior.

This commit covers the testing coverage of existing ips policies.

Partial implement blueprint policy-defaults-refresh

is allowed for everyone.

commit_message:
Fix os-ips policy to be admin_or_owner

os-ips API policy is default to admin_or_owner[1] but API
is allowed for everyone.

We can see the test trying with other project context can access the API
- https://review.opendev.org/#/c/715477

This is because API does not pass the server project_id in policy target[2]
and if no target is passed then, policy.py add the default targets which is
nothing but context.project_id (allow for everyone who try to access)[3]

This commit fix this policy by passing the server's project_id in policy
target.

Closes-bug: #1869396
[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/eaf08c0b7b8250408e5d10c6471f2e3155cc0edb/nova/policies/ips.py#L27

Change-Id: Ie7bcb6537f90813cc5b23d69c886037d25b15a42

commit_message:
Require mock

tempest uses mock and users of tempest need mock as well. Move mock to
requirements so that tempest can be used without extra imports.

Example failure is tempest-stress that does not use mock but only
imports tempest, see https://review.opendev.org/#/c/715613/

Change-Id: Ib7db5160d5d5ead0c70115da5964634363ff9944

commit_message:
Bump hacking to 3.0.0

The new version enables a lot of standard flake8 checks. Some of them
are temporary disabled to reduce the scope of this patch:
* Complexity check requires a few functions to be rewritten (apparently,
  it was not enabled previously).
* Indentation check failures are numerous and potentially contradictive.
These checks will be enabled in follow-ups.

W606 is removed from excludes since we no longer hit it.

Change-Id: I1e5a6f8e5e90c55cfc6f740b26c30196512d3be3

commit_message:
Prevent scripts from exiting when there is no error

This patch is a partial fix of bug:
"k8s atomic/cores driver is not working when tls_disabled='true'"
https://storyboard.openstack.org/#!/story/2007039

Since commit "05c27f2d [k8s][fedora atomic] Rolling upgrade support"
it joins multi deployment scripts into one big heat deployment script.
Each script must be taken care that it doesn't exit in normal case, aka
exit 0, otherwise the big script heat deployment script will exit
immediately, the rest part script will not run.

Task: 37876
Story: 2007039

Change-Id: I10322322a3e39f0e6b44c6d51497cc8226266e4f

Fix up installation instructions for openSUSE

Also correct spelling of the company while we're at it.
The upper-case SUSE is the company name since January 2004.

See https://www.suse.com/brandcentral/suse/identity.php
for details.

commit_message:
Only do nova cell discovery when nova endpoint exists

Nova will soon be switched off on the undercloud, so baremetal
playbooks cannot assume that nova is used. This change only runs cell
discovery when there is a nova endpoint in the catalog.

Change-Id: I97d9412c57da23f8783d2eaa4b56dea7edf11746
Blueprint: nova-less-deploy

commit_message:
Extend install_bootloader command timeout

Adds a new command_timeout_factor argument to the
agent client _command method with a default value of 1,
and sets the install_bootloader command to send a value of 2
to extend the timeout factor to give the agent time to complete
its work before giving up on installing the bootloader and
automatically retrying.

Change-Id: Iab72903c3d30b0ae5b80a5115fc635179869eeee
Story: 2007483
Task: 39201
(cherry picked from commit 4829df2966190595feb69623792678816bdcd6a2)

commit_message:
Refactor methods in cinder store

Some of the methods in cinder store are only used by the Store class
methods and not used outside.
It makes sense to bound them to the class.
This refactoring will also help in handling the None imports inside
the class configure methods which will be done in a followup.

This patch also updates cinderclient version from v2(deprecated) to
v3(current).

Change-Id: I576b787012e73ebaf3274cfd8c31f79894284891

commit_message:
[stable-only] Cap stestr for python 2

stestr dropped python 2 support with version 3.0.0 and tooz does not
use constraints from openstack/requirements, so test-requirements.txt
is updated to use stestr<3.0.0 in case of python 2.

Since tooz do not consume upper-constraints there is no need for
requirement check job either so it is removed, too.

Change-Id: I7a75be587efc2098e919f1ea34f9ffc357203dfb

commit_message:
Fix ANSIBLE_FORKS env variable in ceph-ansible workbook

The right variable to properly set the ansible forks used when
ceph-ansible is triggered is ANSIBLE_FORKS.
This patch just fixes the variable name.

Change-Id: I29c525c13759d1b244b4396ab31f9a92a06cf0f1
Closes-Bug: #1869764

commit_message:
Expect python3 client package in CentOS8

In CentOS, we expect to have python3 client package in 8.x while we
expect to have python2 in 7.x .
Fix unit tests to expect the correct version according to os major
version.

Change-Id: Ie02f59aa876c5b3c9de7cd051551b9ef5f7cc087

commit_message:
Update hacking for Python3

The repo is Python 3 now, so update hacking to version 3.0 which
supports Python 3.

Fix:
W605 invalid escape sequence
E117 over-indented
E305 expected 2 blank lines after class or function definition, found 1

Ignore:
W504 line break after binary operator

Change-Id: Iab3fded493e781156ab7ac85aac641bf536361d5

commit_message:
Add Octavia OVN Provider configuration (1 of 2)

This patch enhances Octavia's OVN driver config, so it can connect to
OVN_Northbound DB using TLS.

This is part 1 of 2, where octavia::api::ovn_nb_connection will move
to newly created octavia::provider::ovn::ovn_nb_connection config file.
But that has to be split into 2 parts to avoid breaking the
CI until the THT+pupple-tripleo changes merges [1].

[1]: https://review.opendev.org/#/q/topic:bug/1861886+(status:open+OR+status:merged)

Co-Authored-By: Brent Eagles <beagles@redhat.com>
Related-Bug: #1861886
Change-Id: Id74ef39ff303c9abf8118df203970cd871ed974a
(cherry picked from commit dce599e49898d7973805a389d3abf5048f9f5099)

messages:
[{'account_id': 25238, 'date': '2020-03-31 08:26:54.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 30491, 'date': '2020-03-31 08:33:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Well, I have separate network and control and it works without these set. RMQ should not require nonlocal bind - it uses local IP addresses. The issue must be elsewhere and this is only hiding it.'}, {'account_id': 25238, 'date': '2020-03-31 09:07:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Weird. I can reproduce 100% and also confirmed by other reporter on bug.

I even saw RabbitMQ during a restart loop successfully start during me setting these values.

also worth mentioning that we are using separate interfaces for storage, internal, tenant etc'}, {'account_id': 30491, 'date': '2020-03-31 10:33:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> > > Well, I have separate network and control and it works without
 > > > these set. RMQ should not require nonlocal bind - it uses local

 > on
 > > bug.
 > >
 > > I even saw RabbitMQ during a restart loop successfully start
 > during
 > > me setting these values.
 > >
 > > I am using CentOS 7
 > 
 > also worth mentioning that we are using separate interfaces for
 > storage, internal, tenant etc

CentOS 7 all the way here. Deployed on Stein and upgraded to Train. It could be I have just been lucky.

That said, I will address this, looks worrying as RabbitMQ seriously shouldn't require this configured. It's for haproxy to bind VIP address. RabbitMQ should not bind it really. If it tries binding something else, then it's a problem as well. The tricky part is RabbitMQ relying on name resolution so bad records in DNS servers can cause this as well. All in all, this will hide the real underlying issue. Even if it seemingly helps pass deploy step.

Also note, -1 is surely not that I don't want this fixed, just that it's IMHO bad direction."}, {'account_id': 25238, 'date': '2020-03-31 11:04:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> 
 > CentOS 7 all the way here. Deployed on Stein and upgraded to Train.
 > It could be I have just been lucky.
Fresh install on Train here. Have previously done installs with Rocky that did not exhibit issue.
 > 
 > That said, I will address this, looks worrying as RabbitMQ
 > seriously shouldn't require this configured. It's for haproxy to
 > bind VIP address. RabbitMQ should not bind it really. If it tries
 > binding something else, then it's a problem as well. The tricky
 > part is RabbitMQ relying on name resolution so bad records in DNS
 > servers can cause this as well. All in all, this will hide the real
 > underlying issue. Even if it seemingly helps pass deploy step.
 > 

Yes and it immediately resolves issue... 

Agree that it is weird since it is binding on the ip which should not require that setting. I discovered it by finding a recommendation to remove the ENV variable that sets IP, and then backtracking what changed between a deploy with Control and Network on same node and a deploy with Control and Network separated.
 > Also note, -1 is surely not that I don't want this fixed, just that
 > it's IMHO bad direction.

Understood. Ofc."}, {'account_id': 30491, 'date': '2020-03-31 16:49:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

 > >

 > > bind VIP address. RabbitMQ should not bind it really. If it tries

 > > part is RabbitMQ relying on name resolution so bad records in DNS
 > > servers can cause this as well. All in all, this will hide the
 > real
 > > underlying issue. Even if it seemingly helps pass deploy step.
 > >
 > 
 > Yes and it immediately resolves issue...
 > 
 > Agree that it is weird since it is binding on the ip which should
 > not require that setting. I discovered it by finding a
 > recommendation to remove the ENV variable that sets IP, and then
 > backtracking what changed between a deploy with Control and Network
 > on same node and a deploy with Control and Network separated.
 > > Also note, -1 is surely not that I don't want this fixed, just
 > that
 > > it's IMHO bad direction.
 > 
 > Understood. Ofc.

In the meantime, could you share (best in the bug report) the output of ss/netstat on the affected hosts after rmq starts running (possibly with -p switch to be able to identify processes) and also relevant ip addressing and what 'getent hosts <BADDIEHOSTNAME>' displays too?"}]

[{'created': '2020-03-31 08:26:54.000000000', 'message': 'Configure sysctl settings for RabbitMQ to fix startup errors

When separating Compute and Network nodes, RabbitMQ may fail to start.

This is caused by the node lacking a required `ip_nonlocal_bind`
sysctl setting.
These settings are set in HAProxy, so if you are deploying with
Compute and Network on the same node, these settings would already be
there.

But if you are separating Compute and Network nodes, these sysctl
are never set and RabbitMQ crashes.

Change-Id: I8c55b940b013e1b3bd276eb0ddd76e53372b45d7
Closes-Bug: #1855935
Signed-off-by: Magnus Lööf <magnus.loof@basalt.se>
'}]
commit_message:
Configure sysctl settings for RabbitMQ to fix startup errors

When separating Compute and Network nodes, RabbitMQ may fail to start.

This is caused by the node lacking a required `ip_nonlocal_bind`
sysctl setting.
These settings are set in HAProxy, so if you are deploying with
Compute and Network on the same node, these settings would already be
there.

But if you are separating Compute and Network nodes, these sysctl
are never set and RabbitMQ crashes.

Change-Id: I8c55b940b013e1b3bd276eb0ddd76e53372b45d7
Closes-Bug: #1855935
Signed-off-by: Magnus Lööf <magnus.loof@basalt.se>

commit_message:
Create a new playbook that will be used for deriving parameters

This change introduces a playbook that will be built on-top of to replace the
workflow `tripleo.derive_params.v1.derive_parameters`. At this time the playbook
is a reference implementation has no ability to compute specific fomulas used
to dervice HCI and NFV parameters, however, in follow commits the needed
functionality will be built out.

Story: 2007419
Task: 39120

Depends-On: I26ea1c01e17513d001e311d68fd239d3ba8c8a0d
Change-Id: I197278211152a589572e789f98ed68631ab20ee5
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kecarter@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Deprecating VMax Volume Config

VMax is now PowerMax and config options have changed
since newton.

The use of resource cinder::backend::dellemc_vmax_iscsi is
not supported anymore. Use cinder::backend::dellemc_powermax
instead.

Change-Id: I9d12fad3094261f0c747f74f4b50c68a4cf476df

revisions:
[{'created': '2020-03-26 12:31:05.000000000', 'message': 'Add bulk IP address assignment to ipam driver

Create a method for bulk assignment of IP addresses within the ipam
driver, to support bulk creation of ports.

This also changes the logic for how the window of available IP addresses
to assign from is calculated within the neutrondb IPAM driver.  The
Python random module is used to produce a statistically sampled set of
IP addresses out of the set of available IPs; this will facilitate
collission avoidance.  When requesting multiple IP addresses the
selection window sized is increased significantly to ensure a larger
number of available IPs, but caps are placed on the amount to make sure
we do not transgress system limits when building pools of IPv6
addresses.

Change-Id: Iad8088eaa261b07153fa358ae34b9a2442bc2a3e
Implements: blueprint speed-up-neutron-bulk-creation
(cherry picked from commit 06e38be42e3996eb8c142c657aa80c825e767f6d)
'}]
commit_message:
Add bulk IP address assignment to ipam driver

Create a method for bulk assignment of IP addresses within the ipam
driver, to support bulk creation of ports.

This also changes the logic for how the window of available IP addresses
to assign from is calculated within the neutrondb IPAM driver.  The
Python random module is used to produce a statistically sampled set of
IP addresses out of the set of available IPs; this will facilitate
collission avoidance.  When requesting multiple IP addresses the
selection window sized is increased significantly to ensure a larger
number of available IPs, but caps are placed on the amount to make sure
we do not transgress system limits when building pools of IPv6
addresses.

Change-Id: Iad8088eaa261b07153fa358ae34b9a2442bc2a3e
Implements: blueprint speed-up-neutron-bulk-creation
(cherry picked from commit 06e38be42e3996eb8c142c657aa80c825e767f6d)

commit_message:
Consistent timestamp format for all datasources

All timestamps in Vitrage should be of the same format:
'%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ'

This is needed so webhooks will know what format to expect.

Story: 1776181
Task: 22405

Depends-On: I27624b28e8aa1770d805ee68982509894522b8e6
Change-Id: I9849ce0850de46f928a7c01009c7738976aa3478

commit_message:
Use correct novajoin package for centos8 featureset 39 freeipa

As see in v7 of test at [1] the installation fails as there is no
python-novajoin for centos8 (python3-novajoin). Tracked by tripleo-ci
squad in [2].

[1] https://review.rdoproject.org/r/#/c/25796/7
[2] https://hackmd.io/7MBqFHurTA2e5H8kYRwgag?both#Reviews-still-in-play-to-addmove-jobs

Change-Id: I9121ab3777101ae67b619b89c9e86171c9d5a77c

[{'created': '2019-11-25 22:02:16.000000000', 'message': 'Use the cloudname for public certmonger certs

In the standalone config, there is no external network defined.
This leaves the hieradata cloud_name_external undefined, resulting in
an error when we using the haproxy-public-tls-certmonger template
to create new public certs through haproxy.

cloud_name_external is just set to the Cloudname, so just use this
parameter instead.

Change-Id: I8778402bbb7a670c4aa95671c6017dff356238d4

commit_message:
Create a new parameter for the HAProxy external network

In the standalone config, there is no external network defined.
This leaves the hieradata cloud_name_external undefined, resulting in
an error when we are using the haproxy-public-tls-certmonger template
to create new public certs through haproxy.

Using the PublicNetwork allows us to get the right network for haproxy
in all cases to specify the network and fqdn to use for public certmonger
certificates.

Co-Authored-By: Grzegorz Grasza <xek@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I8778402bbb7a670c4aa95671c6017dff356238d4

commit_message:
hardware: 'numa_fit_instance_to_host' requires 'limits' argument

The 'NUMATopologyLimits' object, and dictionary representations of same,
are how nova considers host specific RAM and CPU overcommit ratios when
trying to determine whether an instance will fit on a host (in the
'NUMATopologyFilter' scheduler filter) and to actually fit the instance
to the host. They must always be provided and defaulting these to 'None'
makes this confusing. Remove the default value and add type hints for
future reference.

Part of blueprint use-pcpu-and-vcpu-in-one-instance

Change-Id: Iae063c1e67fdf0093ed6549e339287d7daa7265c
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Update master for stable/train

Add file to the reno documentation build to show release notes for
stable/train.

Use pbr instruction to increment the minor version number
automatically so that master versions are higher than the versions on
stable/train.

Change-Id: If73e70bf2bb396ef30b4f38d315bbc284f5bef9f

commit_message:
[OpenStackAnsible] Transition Rocky to EM

This transition the rocky branch to extended maintenance.
Changes for bugfixes and things the team deems important are
still encouraged, but there will no longer be official releases
off of the branch.

Please +1 if the team is ready for us to proceed with this
transition, or -1 if there are any final backports currently in
flight that we should wait for. For the latter case, please
update the patch with the new commit hash after doing a final
release to get those changes out so we know to proceed with the
transition.

Change-Id: I121b241b4457459dbfe4edfd42af08162fa076e2

commit_message:
Oslo releases for 2020-03-30

Major for castellan because one of the changes removes a public member
from some of their modules. Feature for oslo.vmware because I think
the change has an implied dependency bump on the Glance client, even
though the client is passed in and not explicitly listed in the
requirements file.

Change-Id: I9ad3b891c09dab47e38de4d77dcea6d3b1516bf8

commit_message:
Live log for SoftwareDeployment scripts

At present, when heat-container-agent is executing SoftwareDeployment
scripts, the output of this is not visible to the cluster administrator
until the execution is complete. This is an unhelpful behaviour, as it
is far more useful to see what is happening in real time. This change
logs output to files under /var/log/heat-config/heat-config-script/.
Also keep origin logs so we can make sure we won't break backward
compatibility.

reference: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/707694/

Change-Id: I56f7a7b9d404e7e1162c0992463cbab583ae6782

commit_message:
Optimize DVR related port DB query

Save order by in port query when not require fixed_ips,
and save some useless query for dvr subnet mac.

Closes-Bug: #1834308

'}, {'created': '2020-03-27 08:14:59.000000000', 'message': 'Fix serialization of structures that might contain YAQL types

* When YAQL output data conversion is disabled there's still
  an issue caused by presence of not JSON-compatible types within
  a YAQL result. The internal Mistral code is already able to deal
  with that (due to the previous changes) by checking that and
  converting them to what's needed. However, JSON serialization
  may still not work if it's done via the standard "json" library.
  The library simply doesn't handle those non-standard types and
  raises an exception. We have a sanitizing function that all YAQL
  results go through, however, it doesn't make sense to do recursive
  sanitizing for performance reasons. It does make sense to convert
  data as late as possible to avoid redundant data manipulations. So
  the sanitizing function handles only the root object in the object
  graph. The solution for this problem is to use our own utility
  function based on the "oslo_serialization.jsonutils" that is able
  to deal with at least part of the mentioned types, specifically
  FrozenDict and iterators. Generators are still a problem and this
  new function takes care of that separately, assuming that any
  generator is just a special iterator and hence represents a
  collection, i.e. a list in JSON terms. It works for all the cases
  we've encountered so far working with YAQL.
* Used the new function "utils.to_json_str()" everywhere for JSON
  serialization, including the action "std.http".
* Added necessary unit tests.

Closes-Bug: #1869168

commit_message:
Fix serialization of structures that might contain YAQL types

* When YAQL output data conversion is disabled there's still
  an issue caused by presence of not JSON-compatible types within
  a YAQL result. The internal Mistral code is already able to deal
  with that (due to the previous changes) by checking that and
  converting them to what's needed. However, JSON serialization
  may still not work if it's done via the standard "json" library.
  The library simply doesn't handle those non-standard types and
  raises an exception. We have a sanitizing function that all YAQL
  results go through, however, it doesn't make sense to do recursive
  sanitizing for performance reasons. It does make sense to convert
  data as late as possible to avoid redundant data manipulations. So
  the sanitizing function handles only the root object in the object
  graph. The solution for this problem is to use our own utility
  function based on the "oslo_serialization.jsonutils" that is able
  to deal with at least part of the mentioned types, specifically
  FrozenDict and iterators. Generators are still a problem and this
  new function takes care of that separately, assuming that any
  generator is just a special iterator and hence represents a
  collection, i.e. a list in JSON terms. It works for all the cases
  we've encountered so far working with YAQL.
* Used the new function "utils.to_json_str()" everywhere for JSON
  serialization, including the action "std.http".
* Added necessary unit tests.

Closes-Bug: #1869168
Depends-On: I1081a44a6f305eb1dfe68a5bad30110385130725
Change-Id: I9e73ea7cbba215c3e1d174b5189be27c640c4d42

commit_message:
Bump oslo.serialization version to 2.21.1

* Starting version 2.21.1 oslo.serialization adds the parameter
  "fallback" to its "jsonutils.to_primitive" method. We need it
  to address some issue related to JSON serialization.

Change-Id: I1081a44a6f305eb1dfe68a5bad30110385130725

commit_message:
Fix Exception string arguments

Need to use % for arguments to Exception().

W0715: Exception arguments suggest string formatting might
       be intended (raising-format-tuple)

Trivialfix

Change-Id: I1afc2e4a3b34e548247e8a499fe45602454f36f5

commit_message:
Pick stale amphora randomly

Avoid getting the same amphora all the time if its loadbalancer
stuck in PENDING state and could not be failovered.

Story: 2007340
Task: 38877

Change-Id: I2f680a00be695c3828166e6803882765af79b79e
(cherry picked from commit 0f7d03feca4e3a4796c9c1a5a55d8da2adc44ebd)

Monkey patch original current_thread _active

Monkey patch the original current_thread to use the up-to-date _active
global variable. This solution is based on that documented at:
https://github.com/eventlet/eventlet/issues/592

commit_message:
Normalize the 'undercloud-passwords.conf' return data

This change normalizes our client return formation by ensuring we're always
using the configured output path as defined within our constants.

Closes-Bug: #1868619

Change-Id: Ied051214c4d3f2a695d58a6cde6180f040ca02d4
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kecarter@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Default IRONIC_RAMDISK_TYPE to dib

We limit the use of tinyipa to the most intensive jobs:
standalone
grenade
multinode

Also leaving ironic-tempest-ipa-wholedisk-bios-agent_ipmitool-tinyipa
running for now as there could be an issue with the
ironic-python-agent

Story: 2007356
Task: 38908

commit_message:
Introduce 'MIXED' CPU allocation policy for instance

Currently we have 'DEDICATED' and 'SHARED' policies for instance CPU
allocation from host CPUs. 'MIXED' is another CPU allcation policy
for the instance obtaining some 'dedicated' CPUs, that's pinning to
particular host CPU and used exclusively by the instance, and some
'sharing' host CPUs, which will be sharing with other instances.

Also introduce the interface of flavor extra spec 'hw:dedicated_cpus'
for specifiying the bitmask of 'dedicated' instance CPUs.

Change-Id: Ide2eab6dfb0d2100d0f5501ed2a4070b9201320f

commit_message:
Importing keyrings from files rather than from mons

This change permits users to specify a directory where the keyrings are
located.
It is useful when openstack-ansible have no ssh access to the ceph
cluster.

Change-Id: I6693a7f9d0bc7fe1e20eee53a96de8df8985e148

allocation policy, so all 'cpu_pinning_requested' fields within one

commit_message:
Remove 'InstanceNUMACell.cpu_pinning_requested' field

The 'InstanceNUMACell.cpu_pinning_requested' is 'True' if cpu_policy
is 'dedicated', it is also ensured that all NUMA cells have only CPU
allocation policy, so all 'cpu_pinning_requested' fields within one
instance have the same value. And we also have a property in
'InstanceNUMATopology' object with the same name and in the same
value. So duplication exists among these properties, remove
the property in 'InstanceNUMACell' to resolve it.

Change-Id: Ia5aaaf38499da918d0d8cfda1b61e2a7c5bb6666

commit_message:
Refactor the code in checking available host CPUs

In '_numa_fit_instance_cell', the availability of host
dedicated and shared CPUs are checked to ensure host
has enough dedicated CPUs, probably listing in `[compute].'
'cpu_dedicated_set', for instance CPUs requesting a
pinning and the emulator thread if its allocation
policy is 'ISOLATE', and to ensure the host has enough
shared CPUs, probably listing in `[compute].cpu_shared_set`,
for instance sharing CPUs.

For instance taking `dedicated` policy or `shared` CPU
allocation policy, it is only necessary to check the
availability of either dedicated CPUs or shared CPUs.
While for an instance in `mixed` policy will request
both types of CPUs, this patch refactor this part of code
and checks if host satisfies the request of both type
CPUs.

Change-Id: I1715fc99df3c747312dad1e980a1211427f0fa52

'cpu_pinning_requested' property could be derived directly from cpu_policy

'dedicated' cpu_policy. No need to mock the 'cpu_pininng_requested'

[{'created': '2020-03-17 00:55:27.000000000', 'message': "scheduler: Introduce 'dedicated' and 'sharing' CPUs for InstanceNUMACell

After the final host chosen decision made by nova-scheduler, the
'InstanceNUMACell.cpu_pinning' field contains the information of
which instance CPU is pinned on which host CPU. And the scheduler
looks for the instance CPU requeeting a pinning from the
'InstanceNUMACell.cpuset' field considering the fact that all
instance CPUs are 'dedicated'(or pinning) CPUs for a instance
take a CPU allocation pollicy other than 'SHARED'.

Here we want scheduler firstly checks the 'cpu_pinning' field,
and looks for the CPUs for pinning from its key if the fileld
is not none. This supports to let part of instance CPUs to be
'dedicated' ones, and the remaining instance CPUs being 'shared'
ones, which will use host CPUs sharing with other instances.g

Change-Id: I385e78bcd07eb3f4c311bc942b6a04ff8007f6a5
"}, {'created': '2020-03-24 14:30:00.000000000', 'message': "Take the instance dedicated CPU list from 'cpu_pinning' if possible

This patch aims to extend the usage of 'InstanceNUMACell.cpu_pinning'
field to keep the instance NUMA cell dedicated CPU list at the
'InstanceNUMACell' object initializing stage. Thus we could create
an instance with partial CPUs being the dedicated CPUs and the rest
being the shared CPUs, which will be introduced as the 'mixed'
instance CPU allocation policy in the following patches.

The 'cpu_pinning' is a dictionary type object, after the
nova-scheduler finally determined the host CPUs that the instance
threads will work on, each item of this dictionary contains an
instance CPU ID and host CPU ID, with the instance CPU ID in the
key, and host CPU ID in value. But the host CPU ID is unknown
before the nova-scheduler involves, for this case, a value '-1'
in the host CPU ID field will be used in later patches, which
means the host CPU for the instance's dedicated CPU is not
determined.

For instance with existing 'dedicated' or 'shared' CPU allocation
policy, the 'cpu_pinning' field will not be used. And all instance
CPUs are dedicated CPUs if CPU allocation policy is 'dedicated',
these rules are not changed.

Change-Id: I385e78bcd07eb3f4c311bc942b6a04ff8007f6a5

commit_message:
Take the instance dedicated CPU list from 'cpu_pinning' if possible

This patch aims to extend the usage of 'InstanceNUMACell.cpu_pinning'
field to keep the instance NUMA cell dedicated CPU list at the
'InstanceNUMACell' object initializing stage. Thus we could create
an instance with partial CPUs being the dedicated CPUs and the rest
being the shared CPUs, which will be introduced as the 'mixed'
instance CPU allocation policy in the following patches.

The 'cpu_pinning' is a dictionary type object, after the
nova-scheduler finally determined the host CPUs that the instance
threads will work on, each item of this dictionary contains an
instance CPU ID and host CPU ID, with the instance CPU ID in the
key, and host CPU ID in value. But the host CPU ID is unknown
before the nova-scheduler involves, for this case, a value '-1'
in the host CPU ID field will be used in later patches, which
means the host CPU for the instance's dedicated CPU is not
determined.

For instance with existing 'dedicated' or 'shared' CPU allocation
policy, the 'cpu_pinning' field will not be used. And all instance
CPUs are dedicated CPUs if CPU allocation policy is 'dedicated',
these rules are not changed.

Change-Id: I385e78bcd07eb3f4c311bc942b6a04ff8007f6a5

commit_message:
Rescan after restarting the md device

If an md device is restarted, there is a chance, depending
on the OS, that the partition may not be found upon start
of the md device.

Instead, we should always rescan after re-assembling the raid
device.

Story: 2007275
Task: 38712
Change-Id: I92bac20812940e04381a54ef2905ef5f6e293813

[{'created': '2020-03-27 14:22:10.000000000', 'message': 'Better deduplicate hosts entries created for VIPs

VIPs in /etc/hosts resolve to FQDN only, while other entries are also added
with its shortnames. This makes deduplication of entries inefficient:

$ openstack stack output show standalone HostsEntry -f json

"output_value": [
    "192.168.24.1 standalone.localdomain standalone",
    "192.168.24.1 standalone.ctlplane.localdomain standalone.ctlplane",
    "192.168.24.1  standalone.ctlplane.localdomain" # <-- not good!
]

Improve adding VIPs so that it also can be deduped from /etc/hosts

Change-Id: Id9b0ccfacc2666709d3a221b63fcf16fa1c0ae75
Related-bug: #1869375
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

$ openstack stack output show standalone HostsEntry -f json

"output_value": [
    "192.168.24.1 standalone.localdomain standalone",
    "192.168.24.1 standalone.ctlplane.localdomain standalone.ctlplane",
    "192.168.24.1  standalone.ctlplane.localdomain" # <-- not good!
]

Add shortnames for VIPs so that it also can be deduped from /etc/hosts

Change-Id: Id9b0ccfacc2666709d3a221b63fcf16fa1c0ae75
Related-bug: #1869375

commit_message:
Better deduplicate hosts entries created for VIPs

VIPs in /etc/hosts resolve to FQDN only, while other entries are also added
with its shortnames. This makes deduplication of entries inefficient:

$ openstack stack output show standalone HostsEntry -f json

"output_value": [
    "192.168.24.1 standalone.localdomain standalone",
    "192.168.24.1 standalone.ctlplane.localdomain standalone.ctlplane",
    "192.168.24.1  standalone.ctlplane.localdomain" # <-- not good!
]

Add shortnames for VIPs so that it also can be deduped from /etc/hosts

Change-Id: Id9b0ccfacc2666709d3a221b63fcf16fa1c0ae75
Related-bug: #1869375
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
[opensuse]Add configuration for trusts enablement

This patch adds some configuration needed when trusts are enabled and
also enables the external loadbalancer configuration when it is enabled.

Change-Id: Id54e8be8194b9a63f51ad69dd32f8592a5de5c00

commit_message:
Automatically assign floating IPs with LBaaS v2

Kubernetes has a feature to automatically assign floating IPs for
load balancers which has been in the codebase since 1.2.0.  This
means that load balancers will automatically get an external
network.

This patch moves the validation and lookup of external network into
a common location so it can be reused, makes Kubernetes base template
detect network names and convert them to IDs for the Heat template
in order to be able to inject it to the Kubernetes cloud configuration.

Closes-Bug: #1714272
Change-Id: I501f111dee72e8a7c076ef436db4172c1f1fdc6a

With --horizontal-pod-autoscaler-use-rest-clients=true HPA uses

commit_message:
Enable HPA featrue with heapster for kubernetes cluster

With --horizontal-pod-autoscaler-use-rest-clients=true HPA uses
new resource metrics API instead of getting heapster metrics.
If we want to use the metrics from heapster, it should be false(
default to true).
Related to: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/57673

Change-Id: I9488fe1b8cdf879e6f274cbdf6553a0617ebd8e9

commit_message:
Specify storage driver in /etc/sysconfig/docker-storage

Magnum should specify the storage driver in /etc/sysconfig/docker-storage
before running docker-storage-setup.
Currently we just specify generic docker storage driver(like overlay),
but forget "devicemapper".

Change-Id: I0eee1b568060d0153971575509d27123997a1949

commit_message:
Do not scope to OS-TRUST when no TRUST_ID is given

When cluster_user_trust is False no TRUST_ID is set causing an invalid
request to be sent to keystone. If no TRUST_ID is given it is sufficient
to authenticate with just the user/password if magnum is configured
with a project_domain_name and user_domain_name.

Change-Id: Ieb1e42d0f8c16eaed276e57e05833c624573ac7c

commit_message:
Add k8s_centos_ironic_v1 driver

Currently, k8s cluster created by Magnum supports Fedora and
CoreOS as guest OS for Master and Minion nodes.
This commit enables support for CentOS as guest OS for Master and
Minion nodes to deploy k8s cluster through magnum.

Change-Id: I031efebf1f9c152919bcbadea95ba3a447be7638

commit_message:
kubernetes: add retry logic for atomic installs

It is possible that during the deployment, DockerHub fails for
some reason and the installation stalls out.  This adds a retry
login which will retry for 5 times with a 15 second timeout before
failing.

Story: #2002589
Task: #28337
Change-Id: Ide503850755b2e1bd80cd1c028b7fcaf89f62a5e

commit_message:
Correct configurations for kubelet and kube-proxy

There are a few of wrong configurations for kubelet and kube-proxy
when TLS is disabled:
1. In file kubelet-config.yaml, line "user:" should not be deleted.
2. In file proxy-config.yaml, "client-certificate", "client-key",
    "certificate-authority" should be deleted.
3. In file /etc/kubernetes/kubelet, options "--client-ca-file",
    "--tls-cert-file", "--tls-private-key-file" should be deleted.

Change-Id: Id71909b971dddd36ec758975a381454eec5ef943
Closes-bug: #1792663

commit_message:
[WIP] Remove deprecated services

Services marked for deprecation:
* Heapster
* Influx
* Grafana
* Dashboard

With the installation of the new monitoring solution
the previous influx-grafana deployment based on heapster
is no longer needed. This patch tracks the deletion of
the unneeded services that are replaced by this chart
but that are kept to allow for backward compatibility.

Story: 2004623
depends_on: I80d590785bf30f9d634debeaf51c0d4cce0aeb93
Signed-off-by: Diogo Guerra <dy090.guerra@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ib5161e6674bb0d12aa461eeb924d436d37b4826d

commit_message:
change order of  enable_services

In kubemaster.yml[1] file services are enabled and started before network
config, so it should be after network config. Order of enable services is
updated.
[1]https://github.com/openstack/magnum/blob/master/magnum/drivers/ \
k8s_fedora_atomic_v1/templates/kubemaster.yaml

Change-Id: I420b2da2aaa9bb5dc45b896a4cd846d84374d4b4

commit_message:
[k8s] Install Kubernetes dashboard with helm

Following our development on the use of helm, let's install kubernetes cluster dashboard using the upstream chart stable/kubernetes-dashboard

Currently the CPU/Memory metrics are not available with the metrics-server.
A PR is on the way to fix this issue, and there is already available a fix for preview.
Check> https://github.com/kubernetes/dashboard/pull/3504

Change-Id: Ic7f1a3922acb065e94959148679f3098d43cb773
Story: 2004816
Task: 29603
Signed-off-by: Diogo Guerra <dy090.guerra@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Introduce driver-specific cluster labels

Today cluster labels list is hardcoded for all drivers
even a driver doesn't have some values which are specific
for a different driver.
To avoid 'The parameter (___) was not defined in template'
exception drivers list is no longer hardcoded and it is
split into two parts: first one is common lables and second
one is driver-specific labels. Those parts can be redefined
for a specific driver.

Change-Id: Iee69d4a1efa0596a6a3d70eb5a4eaf40e9ba96b4
Closes-Bug: #1764700
Related-Bug: #1722523

commit_message:
Add OVN as a CNI network backend for k8s

OVN is a project that provides virtual networking through Open vSwitch.
This allows to use ovn-kubernetes as a CNI plugin for the k8s fedora driver.

Change-Id: Ie6b9bf64222399de26707882982bdf8a3b0e8ba0
Task: 30982
Story: 2005671

commit_message:
fix pulling image from insecure registry error

to use image from insecure registry when running `atomic install`,
`/etc/containers/registries.con` need to be configured as follow
```
[registries.insecure]
registries = ['$INSECURE_REGISTRY_URL']
```

Task: 30979
Story: 2005668
Change-Id: I68492bf7511df7f1275bea1ca29f58573661ac6e

commit_message:
suport multi discovery service

magnum will try to use discovery url in following order:
1. discovery url which is passed when create a cluster
2. discovery service endpoint in configuration
3. if configurated discovery endpoint is differnent from
   "https://discovery.etcd.io/new?size=%(size)d" and,
   use "https://discovery.etcd.io/new?size=%(size)d" as a backup
   service

Task: 26938
Story:2003994

Change-Id: I915b554ad96cf8f256814d8fac614aa3715fc4e1

This reverts commit 2ba0cbce4182923fa58db087fb946c83fc7fa5b9.

* It is undesirable that the end user can inject proxy config into
  the magnum-conductor service via the cluster template.

  the same as those which are required in the cluster template for

environment variables for proecesses, and this should be used by the
cloud operator / deployment tooling to configure the required proxy
settings for the magnum-conductor service.

In particular this patch makes it impossible for the cloud operator
to specify their own http_proxy via the environment, the user supplied
cluster template setting will always be used.

commit_message:
Revert "support http/https proxy for discovery url"

[stable branch policy requiring a backport rather than an 'in branch'
revert means that the following revert SHA refers to the parent patch,
not to this branch]

This reverts commit e8d0ee1b144f4db24367ad48bd2cb4306add6672.

This commit is reverted for two reasons:

* It is undesirable that the end user can inject proxy config into
  the magnum-conductor service via the cluster template.

* The proxy settings for the magnum-conductor service may not be
  the same as those which are required in the cluster template for
  the end user VM.

Systemd, docker and podman all include native mechanisms for setting
environment variables for proecesses, and this should be used by the
cloud operator / deployment tooling to configure the required proxy
settings for the magnum-conductor service.

In particular this patch makes it impossible for the cloud operator
to specify their own http_proxy via the environment, the user supplied
cluster template setting will always be used.

conflicts: magnum/drivers/heat/template_def.py

Change-Id: I33da19ad6764bedcf15f2a08381063e2471f8991
(cherry picked from commit 79699f23cddf906753b02562f6d2aebc03e3e15e)
(cherry picked from commit 1c4f8127f183724fb885662e68d1133899c3336c)

Since the release of bandit 1.6.0 the '-x' option seems to have
changed behavior. Previously, to match a path like 'magnum/tests/*',
you could state '-x test'. This option now expects a glob patterns,

commit_message:
Fix pep8 issues caused by bandit version 1.6.0

Since the release of bandit 1.6.0 the '-x' option seems to have
changed behavior. Previously, to match a path like 'magnum/tests/*',
you could state '-x test'. This option now expects a glob patterns,
such as '-x magnum/tests/*'.

Change-Id: I274a366f0f87cca96177ccf8f137f9f489f05b60
Story: #2005696
Task: #31017

[{'created': '2019-06-25 08:07:43.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "support http/https proxy for discovery url"

This reverts commit f86de684d2dcca018d056c44be4e4b164b8a4b32.

This commit is reverted for two reasons:

* It is undesirable that the end user can inject proxy config into
  the magnum-conductor service via the cluster template.

* The proxy settings for the magnum-conductor service may not be
  the same as those which are required in the cluster template for
  the end user VM.

Systemd, docker and podman all include native mechanisms for setting
environment variables for proecesses, and this should be used by the
cloud operator / deployment tooling to configure the required proxy
settings for the magnum-conductor service.

In particular this patch makes it impossible for the cloud operator
to specify their own http_proxy via the environment, the user supplied
cluster template setting will always be used.

Change-Id: I33da19ad6764bedcf15f2a08381063e2471f8991

commit_message:
Revert "support http/https proxy for discovery url"

[stable branch policy requiring a backport rather than an 'in branch'
revert means that the following revert SHA refers to the parent patch,
not to this branch]

This reverts commit e8d0ee1b144f4db24367ad48bd2cb4306add6672.

This commit is reverted for two reasons:

* It is undesirable that the end user can inject proxy config into
  the magnum-conductor service via the cluster template.

* The proxy settings for the magnum-conductor service may not be
  the same as those which are required in the cluster template for
  the end user VM.

Systemd, docker and podman all include native mechanisms for setting
environment variables for proecesses, and this should be used by the
cloud operator / deployment tooling to configure the required proxy
settings for the magnum-conductor service.

In particular this patch makes it impossible for the cloud operator
to specify their own http_proxy via the environment, the user supplied
cluster template setting will always be used.

conflicts: magnum/drivers/heat/template_def.py

Change-Id: I33da19ad6764bedcf15f2a08381063e2471f8991
(cherry picked from commit 79699f23cddf906753b02562f6d2aebc03e3e15e)
(cherry picked from commit 1c4f8127f183724fb885662e68d1133899c3336c)

commit_message:
[train][goal] Define new magnum-functional-api-ipv6-only job

As part of Train community goal 'Support IPv6-Only Deployments and Testing'[1],
we need to define the integration job which deploy services
on IPv6 and perform testing to make sure service listen and communicate
over IPv6 properly.

Magnum has legacy zuul jobs only so base zuulv3 IPv6 job 'devstack-ipv6' and
'devstack-tempest-ipv6' cannot be used and we have to copy the whole
run.yaml to set the IPv6 setting and run the IPv6 verification
script via post_test_hook.

This commit adds the new job 'magnum-functional-api-ipv6-only'
run on gate and set the required IPv6 setting'.

Story: #2005477
Task: #35902

[1] https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/train/ipv6-support-and-testing.html

Change-Id: I3b9e88a6993a16143cfdbf8499389fca12d4af29

commit_message:
k8s: set functional jobs to voting

Since the fixes to resolve functional tests have merged, there
has been 42 runs of magnum-functional-k8s, out of those, only 3
failed and 2 of those failures were actual failures that caught
a breakage, with one being non-deterministic[1].

The job seems stable enough in order to run with voting in order
to make sure that we never merge code that breaks a deployment
of a new Kubernetes cluster.

[1]: http://zuul.openstack.org/builds?job_name=magnum-functional-k8s&branch=master

Change-Id: Ie0b5bc1f2455ec7ecbb68d8042390a92550706d7

commit_message:
Remove buildimage jobs

Remove buildimage jobs, they have been disabled in April 2019 and the
project uses upstream images now.

Remove them so that the legacy parent job can be removed, this repo
is one of the final users.

Change-Id: Ieb4fe3e6122270b4e9114012dee5af747d88d539
(cherry picked from commit a4190dc9d0bce4a4d7c7633aacf6e282ac5a5128)

commit_message:
Allow default-worker to have node_count=0

With the arrival of nodegroups, this change allows a cluster's
default-worker group to be resized to 0 so that they can be replaced
with new nodegroups.

story: 2007272
task: 38686

Change-Id: I5c6d9b8f1ad8c9c77eb758f225c32d14ce86cac5
Depends-On: Ie91fdfe71058b45c5fd1217920b8b5b993e47734
Signed-off-by: Bharat Kunwar <brtknr@bath.edu>

Revert "openstack-base: pin setuptools < 46 to get horizon working"

commit_message:
Extend install_bootloader command timeout

Adds a new command_timeout_factor argument to the
agent client _command method with a default value of 1,
and sets the install_bootloader command to send a value of 2
to extend the timeout factor to give the agent time to complete
its work before giving up on installing the bootloader and
automatically retrying.

Change-Id: Iab72903c3d30b0ae5b80a5115fc635179869eeee
Story: 2007483
Task: 39201

Create a method for bulk assignment of IP addresses within the ipam
driver, to support bulk creation of ports.

This also changes the logic for how the window of available IP addresses
to assign from is calculated within the neutrondb IPAM driver.  The
Python random module is used to produce a statistically sampled set of
IP addresses out of the set of available IPs; this will facilitate
collission avoidance.  When requesting multiple IP addresses the

commit_message:
Add bulk IP address assignment to ipam driver

Create a method for bulk assignment of IP addresses within the ipam
driver, to support bulk creation of ports.

This also changes the logic for how the window of available IP addresses
to assign from is calculated within the neutrondb IPAM driver.  The
Python random module is used to produce a statistically sampled set of
IP addresses out of the set of available IPs; this will facilitate
collission avoidance.  When requesting multiple IP addresses the
selection window sized is increased significantly to ensure a larger
number of available IPs, but caps are placed on the amount to make sure
we do not transgress system limits when building pools of IPv6
addresses.

Change-Id: Iad8088eaa261b07153fa358ae34b9a2442bc2a3e
Implements: blueprint speed-up-neutron-bulk-creation
(cherry picked from commit 06e38be42e3996eb8c142c657aa80c825e767f6d)
